Windows:
1. Install Glest 3.1.2
2. Extract windows install file into Glest 3.1.2 directory, it will overwrite a
   few files (menu.xml, english.lng, etc.)

Linux:
1. Install Glest 3.1.2
Download:
2. Download tarball and extract into Glest 3.1.2 directory.
-- or --
Compile: 
2. type "cd mk/linux"
3. run "./autogen.sh"
4. run "./configure" (use "configure --help" for options)
5. run "jam" (if running on a multicore system, running "jam -jx" is
   reccomended, where "x" is the number of cores plus one.
6. Copy into Glest 3.1.2 directory by running something similar to the
   following: "tar c glestadv ./data/core/menu/menu.xml ./data/core/menu/textures/textentry.tga ./data/lang/english.lng ./glestadv.ini | tar xC <glest directory>"


